<item>
            <title>[HTTPCLIENT-399] Connection not closed after &quot;Connection: close&quot; request</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-399</link>
                <project id="12310360" key="HTTPCLIENT">HttpComponents HttpClient</project>
                        <description>In HTTP specification at &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.w3.org/Protocols/rfc2616/rfc2616-&quot;&gt;http://www.w3.org/Protocols/rfc2616/rfc2616-&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
sec8.html , under chapter &amp;quot;Negotiation&amp;quot;, it is stated :&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;quot;If either the client or the server sends the close token in the Connection &lt;br/&gt;
header, that request becomes the last one for the connection.&amp;quot;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
HttpClient (v2.0.2 and v3.0 alpha2) is currently closing connection only if &lt;br/&gt;
server has sent &amp;quot;Connection: close&amp;quot; header, and not when request contains it.</description>
                <environment>Operating System: All&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: PC</environment>
